    "what_description": "Lunathyrium lasiopteris is a species of fern in the family Aspleniaceae. It is characterized by its erect or ascending habit, 30-70 cm tall, with linear to lanceolate, entire or dentate pinnae and lanceolate to ovate, deeply lobed to pinnatifid pinnules. The plant has a rhizome with long, thin, hairless scales, and the fertile fronds have a longer stipe, with lanceolate to linear, entire or dentate pinnae and lanceolate to ovate, deeply lobed to pinnatifid pinnules. The sporangia are located on the underside of the pinnules, and the spores are brown, tetrahedral, and 58-66 \u03bcm in diameter. The species is known from China, Japan, and the Philippines, where it grows in shaded, humid areas.",
