    "properties_description": "The main therapeutic properties of Lunathyrium lasiopteris are anti-inflammatory, antimicrobial, and antioxidant, which provide the plant with its medicinal value. The anti-inflammatory property of Lunathyrium lasiopteris is attributed to its bioactive compounds, including flavonoids and saponins, which have been shown to reduce inflammation and alleviate pain. Antimicrobial property of the plant is associated with the presence of volatile oils, such as terpenes and phenolic compounds, which have been found to exhibit antibacterial and antifungal activities. The antioxidant property of Lunathyrium lasiopteris is due to the presence of phenolic compounds, which have been proven to scavenge free radicals and protect against oxidative stress. The bioactive compounds in Lunathyrium lasiopteris also exhibit hepatoprotective and cytotoxic activities, suggesting its potential in the treatment of various diseases.",
