    "constituents_description": "The most important healing constituents of Lunathyrium lasiopteris are flavonoids, particularly quercetin and kaempferol, which exhibit anti-inflammatory and antioxidant activities, reducing swelling and protecting cells from damage.  The plant also contains sesquiterpenoids like lunathyriol, which has been shown to inhibit histamine release and exhibit antimicrobial properties.  Additionally, Lunathyrium lasiopteris contains phenolic acids such as ferulic acid and caffeic acid, which have been found to possess antioxidant and anti-inflammatory properties.  The plant's flavonoids and sesquiterpenoids may also contribute to its analgesic and anti-inflammatory effects, providing relief from pain and inflammation.  These constituents, along with other bioactive compounds present in the plant, contribute to its traditional use in treating various health conditions, including fever, rheumatism, and digestive issues.",
