    "preparations_description": "The main herbal preparations of Lunathyrium lasiopteris are lunaria tea, lunaria tincture, lunaria infusion, lunaria decoction, and lunaria salve. Lunaria tea is a mild preparation made by infusing the plant's leaves in hot water, typically used to treat mild digestive issues. Lunaria tincture is a concentrated liquid extract of the plant's leaves, often used to treat respiratory issues such as bronchitis and asthma. Lunaria infusion is similar to tea but typically requires longer steeping time, used to treat conditions like fever and inflammation. Lunaria decoction is a stronger preparation made by boiling the plant's roots and leaves, often used to treat chronic conditions like arthritis and skin irritations, while lunaria salve is a topical preparation used to treat skin conditions like eczema and wounds.",
